<HEADLINE> Title Race Intense after Dalian Shide Loses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The race for the season's title
tends to get down to the wire as the league leaders Dalian Shide
has their winning momentum stopped by Tianjin Taida at home in the
20th round of the Chinese first division soccer league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Taida overcame one goal deficit to beat Shide 2-1, keeping a
clean record against the league-leading club this season. They
edged Shide 1-0 at home court in the seventh round match.
</P>
<P>
Shide retained its league leading position with 45 points but
failed to pull away from the closest rival Shanghai Shenhua which
pulled off a 2-1 victory over Shenyang Haishi.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua, which now ranked second with 41 points, will keep heat
on Shide in a two-horse title race after the reigning champion
Shandong Luneng lost 2-0 to Jilin Aodong, which is struggling at
the bottom with 16 points.
</P>
<P>
Luneng, which stormed to its first title in club history last
season, has suffered their second straight loss and now stands
third with 35 points.
</P>
<P>
On the other end of the standings, Xiamen Xiaxin remains
languishing after they tied with Sichuan Quanxin 2-2 at home court.
They ranks second from bottom on 17 points.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao Hainiu slid further after they lost 1-4 away to Beijing
Guo'an. With only 19 points from 20 matches, their chance of
staying in the first division next season becomes cloudy.
</P>
<P>
In other matches of the day, Liaoning Fushun beat Yunnan Hongta
2-1 at home and Shenzhen Ping'an forced Chongqing Longxin to a 2-2
road tie. 
</P>
</TEXT>
