<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Wins ITU World Cup in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Australian Loretta Harrop
captured her third straight Triathlon World Cup at the
Tiszaujvaros ITU World Cup Triathlon tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Harrop wrapped up the title in 1 hour 54 minutes and 41 seconds,
36 seconds ahead of the second-placed American Siri Lindley.
Stephanie Forrester of Britain was third in 1:56:53.
</P>
<P>
Martin Krnavek of the Czech Republic won the men's event in 1:
45.28, followed by New Zealander Shane Reed (1:46:03) and
Hungarian Csaba Kuttor (1:46:09). 
</P>
</TEXT>
