<HEADLINE> Albright to visit Brazil, Argentina, Chile, Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright will visit Brazil, Argentina, Chile and Ecuador
next week, the State Department said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Her trip will start between August 15-19 after a meeting with
North American Free Trade Area partners Mexico and Canada in New
Mexico on Saturday and going to Los Angeles on Sunday and Monday
for the opening of the Democratic National Convention, State
Department spokesman Richard Boucher said. 
</P>
