<HEADLINE> US Mission To Visit Colombia for Clinton's Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Undersecretary of State
Thomas Pickering and anti-drug chief Barry McCaffrey will arrive
next Friday to Colombia to prepare the visit of President Bill
Clinton to the South American country on August 30.
</P>
<P>
Colombian Foreign Minister Guillermo Fernandez de Soto Monday
was quoted by the local radio station, CARACOL as saying that they
are going to talk on the visit of President Clinton and to
evaluate consultative mechanisms both governments have set up to
properly develop the binational agenda.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting with Pickering will deal with the issues
related to the economic and military help (1.3 billion U.S.
dollars) Washington is going to provide under the Plan of Colombia,
which deals with the anti-drugs fight, peace with the guerrilla
groups, reactivation of national economy and the strengthening of
democracy.
</P>
<P>
U.S. anti-drugs chief McCaffrey, who will visit Colombia after
a trip around Mexico, is going to analyze with Colombian
authorities the application of the special assistance provided by
the United States to the Plan of Colombia.
</P>
<P>
He will also evaluate the different chapters of the assistance
package in the areas of social and economic development, justice,
human rights and anti-drugs fight, during his meetings with
Colombian President Andres Pastrana and other members of the
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
