<HEADLINE> Uruguayan Meat Exports Up 24 Pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan meat and meat
product exports reached 295 million U.S. dollars during the first
seven months of the year, increasing by 24 percent over the same
period in 1999, the National Meat Institute reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Beef sales abroad reached 233 million dollars with 172,516 tons
, a 30 percent increase over the same period last year. Lamb
exports, amounting to 10,733 tons, increased by 48 percent.
</P>
