<HEADLINE> Germany, Mexico's Third Trade Partner: Embassy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany remains Mexico's
third most important commercial partner after the United States
and Canada, according to the Mexican embassy in Germany.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, Mexico exported 1.489 billion U.S. dollars worth of
goods to Germany, mainly raw materials, and imported 4.523 billion
dollars worth of commodities from that country. 
</P>
