<DOCNO> XIE20000807.0021 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus, EU Sign Economic Assistance Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and the European Union (EU)
signed on Monday a series of agreements on EU economic assistance
to Cyprus, the official Cyprus News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by Cyprus Finance Minister Takis
Clerides and Donato Chiarini, head of the EU delegation in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements, the EU is to provide 1.4 million euros (1.
3 million dollars) for Cyprus' harmonization with EU rules and
regulations, 1.4 million euros (1.3 million dollars) to finance the
participation of Cyprus in a program for research and technological
development and 2.4 million euros (2.2 million dollars) for the
development of civil society.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after the signing of the agreements, Clerides noted
that Cyprus' request had been for "much higher amounts."
</P>
<P>
However, "we are happy to receive this amount," he said, adding
that "we are still looking for other amounts coming our way."
</P>
<P>
Chiarini admitted that the amount provided is below Cyprus'
expenditure for its EU harmonization process, but said "You are
much more prosperous than all the other candidates and also on the
per capita basis the amount is about what the others receive."
</P>
<P>
He added, however, that there was no reason that Cyprus should
not ask for greater support from the EU and he pledged to support
such a request.
</P>
<P>
Chiarini also expressed EU support to greater contacts between
Greek Cypriots and Turkish Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Greek and Turkish Cypriot
communities since 1974 when Turkey invaded and occupied the
northern third of the island after a failed pro-Athens coup.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus applied for EU membership in 1990 and started substantive
accession negotiations with the EU in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
