<HEADLINE> Jerusalem Islamic Rather Than Mere Palestinian Issue: Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait stressed Monday that
Jerusalem was not a mere Palestinian issue but an important Arab
and Islamic cause.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Kuwaiti First Deputy Prime Minister and
Foreign Minister Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber Al-Sabah following a
meeting with visiting United States Assistant Secretary of State
for Far East Affairs Edward Walker.
</P>
<P>
Sabah expressed the hope that the Palestinian and Israeli sides
could reach a just, fair and durable peace.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Emir Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah and Prime Minister
Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Salem Al-Sabah have held separate
meetings with Walker, who arrived here Sunday night for a two-day
visit.
</P>
<P>
Walker conveyed a message from U.S. President Bill Clinton to
the Kuwaiti emir on the failed Camp David talks between Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak under
the auspices of Clinton last week in the U.S..
</P>
<P>
The two-week talks failed to solve final-status issues,
including Jerusalem, statehood, Palestinian refugees, Jewish
settlements, water and security, to pave the way for the conclusion
of a permanent Israeli-Palestinian peace deal.
</P>
<P>
Walker is on a Mideast tour as the U.S. efforts to revive the
peace march on the Palestinian-Israeli track after the failure of
Camp David talks. He has visited Saudi Arabia, Egypt, Jordan,
Lebanon and Syria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
