<HEADLINE> EC Approved Joint Venture to Make Groundbreaking Ruling on Internet Marketplace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission on
Monday approved the business-to-business joint venture of
MyAircraft.com to make a groundbreaking ruling on the Internet
marketplace.
</P>
<P>
The commission, the executive body of the 15-nation bloc, said
that it had found no competition problems with the joint venture
between United Technologies Corp. and Honeywell International Inc.,
both from the United States.
</P>
<P>
The commission said the joint venture would be seen by third
parties as a tool to make the operation within the aerospace
industry quicker, more efficient and less costly.
</P>
<P>
Other B2B marketplaces in the same sector have also been looked
into by the commission that cautioned on Monday that it would
judge other like joint ventures case by case on their respective
merits.
</P>
<P>
Boeing Co., BAe Systems Plc, Lockheed Martin Corp. and Raytheon
Co. announced last month that they were forming an aerospace B2B
joint venture called "Exostar".
</P>
<P>
The European Union has been closely monitoring the mergers and
joint ventures so that none should establish a domination in the
marketplace that rules out the competition from other companies in
the same sector. 
</P>
