<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Greece's equity prices Monday
plunged to their lowest level since early in May 1999, with the
general index on the Athens Stock Exchange (ASE) ending 3.50
percent lower at 3,731.44 points.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index fell 3.13 percent while the FTSE/ASE 40
index finished 4.54 percent lower.
</P>
