<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkish anti-narcotics police
seized on Monday 100 kilograms of heroin in Baskale town of eastern
Van province, Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, the police raided a house in Baskale's
Guroluk village and confiscated the drug buried in the front garden
of the house.
</P>
<P>
Muzaffer Sahin, the owner of the house, was arrested. He
confessed to having brought the heroin from Iran and planning to
take it to Istanbul, the agency reported.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, anti-drug police also seized 22 marijuana
plants and 10 grams of powdered hashish in Iskenderun town of
southern Hatay province and 19,250 marijuana plants in Umutlu
village of Nurhak township in southeastern Kahramanmaras province,
arresting four suspects.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, anti-drug forces have captured
3,219 suspects on drug-related cases and seized 2,850 kilograms of
heroin, 22.6 tons of hashish, 976 kilograms of base morphine, 56
kilograms of opium, 6 kilograms of cocaine, 5.5 tons of acid
anhydride, 618,336 captogan pills and 14,964 synthetic drugs, a
police statement said.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, a total of 6,121 suspects were captured in 2,587 drug-
related cases and anti-drug forces seized 2,249 kilograms of
heroin, 5,458 kilograms of hashish, 288 kilograms of base morphine,
13 kilograms of cocaine, 26.2 tons of acid anhydride and 1,749,305
captogan pills, the statement added. 
