<HEADLINE> Gangsters' Shooting in Tokyo Leaves Two Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A shooting incident broke out when
a group of armed men stormed into an office of a right-wing
organization in central Tokyo on Monday, killing two people and
injuring five others, police said.
</P>
<P>
About 15 knife-wielding attackers broke into the office of the
rightist group Sofusha (Blue Wind Group) and began firing at
around 3:20 p.m., and were met by gunfire by three Sofusha members
in the office, police said.
</P>
<P>
The police later seized two handguns and arrested the three
Sofusha members for possessing firearms. Investigators believed
the incident was a case of intra-group conflict.
</P>
<P>
The knife-wielding gangsters besieged the Sofusha office to
collect loans, the police said.
</P>
<P>
Sofusha, an organization with more than 30 members, was
established in 1983. 
