<HEADLINE> Jenny Thompson Aims for First Olympic Individual Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- After five gold medals all
from relay events, Jenny Thompson is pursuing her first-ever
individual gold in the Olympic Games when the U.S. swimming trials
will start in Indianapolis on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At 27, Thompson who is tied with speedskater Bonnie Blair for
the most Olympic gold medals by an American woman, will enter her
fourth Olympic swimming trials, and mostly likely the last chance
to attempt for an individual title in the quandrennial Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"It's important to me because I feel I'm capable of doing it,"
Thompson said, "If this is my last Olympics, I can know that I'm
ending the closest i can get to my potential."
</P>
<P>
"If I stopped now, I would feel disappointed, not because I
didn't get a gold medal but because i didn't try. I feel I owe it
to myself."
</P>
<P>
Eight years ago, Thompson finished second to Zhuang Yong of
China in the 100-meter freestyle, wherein she even set a world
record four months before, becoming the first swimmer outside
former East Germany to set a world mark in the event in two
decades.
</P>
<P>
Four years ago at the Olympic trials, Thompson missed all the
individual events by finishing the best of the third place in the
100-meter freestyle as only two swimmers qualify for each event.
</P>
<P>
Despite her three gold medals from the relays, her individual
gold remaines elusive after the Atlanta Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Thompson began to reassess her career and has been
swimming faster than ever, using weight training, yoga and
stretching exercises to increase her strength and flexibility.
</P>
<P>
Last year, she set a world record in the 100-meter butterfly of
57.88 seconds, breaking a mark by Mary Meagher that had stood for
18 years.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Thompson broke her own American record in the 100m
freestyle in 54.27, set a personal best of one minute 59.49
seconds in the 200m freestyle and came within two-hundredths of a
second of her best in the 50m freestyle in 25.20 seconds.
</P>
<P>
At the trials which will run through August 16, Thompson will
wear the Fastskin bodysuit made by Speedo to try the individual
freestyle and butterfly events, hoping for an eventual hit for any
Olympic individual gold medal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
