<HEADLINE> Pearl River Delta City's External Trade Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Dongguan City in south China's
Guangdong Province has seen a big surge in its import and export
trade, standing among leading large and medium-sized cities in
external trade in China.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the city's import and export
value amounted to 14.99 billion U.S. dollars, accounting for 19.1
percent of the province.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, exports increased 29.4 percent from a year
earlier to 7.92 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The city's general trade exports reached 81.9 million U.S.
dollars in the six months, a rise of 31.6 percent year on year and
much higher than its processing trade exports.
</P>
<P>
The major export destinations of goods from Dongguan are the
United States, Hong Kong, European Union countries and Japan, with
export values standing at 2.8, 2.11, 1.2 and 0.62 billion U.S.
dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city introduced 594 new industrial projects
involving overseas investment, and actually used a total foreign
investment of 780 million U.S. dollars in the January-June period.
</P>
</TEXT>
