<HEADLINE> Floods Cause Heavy Losses in Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Five successive heavy storms
have hit central China's Henan Province, and resulted in losses of
12 billion yuan (about 1.5 billion U.S. dollars) to the local
economy.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial department of civil affairs, floods
have hit 15 major cities and prefectures in the past two months,
affecting 22.75 million people, about one fourth of Henan's
population.
</P>
<P>
The floods have besieged 1,368 villages, with 767,800
inhabitants, and inundated 1.46 million hectares of crops.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have taken measures to organize the people
for flood-control work and to ensure them sufficient food and
clothing, and medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has allocated emergency funds of 18
million yuan (about 2.2 million U.S. dollars) for the flood
victims.  
</P>
</TEXT>
