<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Rules for Cosmetics Manufacturers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Health recently
issued regulations on the sanitation of cosmetics manufacturers in
an effort to bring the country's fledgling toiletries industry
under control.
</P>
<P>
The document, comprising seven chapters and 46 articles, sets
rules for the location and design of cosmetics factories,
sanitation and storage of raw materials, and the sanitation and
health conditions of factory staff.
</P>
<P>
The workshops must not be located less than 30 meters from any
source of pollution; nor must they affect the normal life of local
residents, according to the regulations.
</P>
<P>
Special equipment to ensure the sanitation of the workshops
must be installed, and discharge of industrial wastes should meet
the relevant national standards, the regulations stipulate.
</P>
</TEXT>
