<HEADLINE> Half-Day Hartal Observed Peacefully in Chittagon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- An eight-hour hartal (destructive
strike) called by All Party Action Committee (APAC), a component
of Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP)-led four-party alliance
passed off peacefully in Chittagong, the largest port city in
Bangladesh, the official Bangladesh News Agency reported here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The hartal which began from 6 a.m. was enforced by the APAC in
protest against the attack on the life of Jatiya Party President
Jahangir Alam.
</P>
<P>
Government and semi-government offices and autonomous bodies
functioned as usual with satisfactory attendance of the officers
and other staff members.
</P>
<P>
Rickshaws plied in the city as normal. Auto-rickshaws and
trucks were also seen plying in port and commercial areas, police
and eyewitnesses said.
</P>
<P>
The inside activities of Chittagong port was normal, while
transportation of goods to and from Chittagong port was hampered
during hartal hours, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Additional police forces have been deployed in almost all
vantage points. Chittagong Metropolitan Police control room
sources said that they did not receive any report of untoward
incidents from any part of the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
