<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Foreign Currency Reserve Assets Up in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The official foreign currency
reserve assets of Hong Kong amounted to 98.9 billion U.S. dollars
at the end of July this year, according to the Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) Monday.
</P>
<P>
The foreign currency reserve assets of Hong Kong in July
included unsettled forward contracts, compared to the 97.1 billion
U.S. dollars at the end of June, this year.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's total foreign currency reserve assets represent
over seven times the currency in circulation or about 40 percent
of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
