<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Hamburg's Ingo Hertzsch is
expected to be called up to the German national team as head coach
Rudi Voller named his squad for an August 16 friendly against
Spain.
</P>
<P>
Voller will announce his 18 man squad at the German Football
Federation's Frankfurt headquarters on Tuesday. Defender Hertzsch
is likely to be the only fresh face to join a team which disgraced
itself at Euro 2000.
</P>
<P>
"Ten years ago I cheered for Voller at the World Cup," the 23-
year-old Hertzsch said. "To play under him for Germany is a once
in a lifetime chance. I have butterflies, it's great motivation."
</P>
<P>
Voller has revealed nothing about his expected line up except
to say there will be "one or two surprises". 
</P>
