<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rare Plants, Animals Found in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Rare plants and animals have been
found in the Dabie Mountains in Hubei Province, central China.
</P>
<P>
The plants, divided into 170 families, 729 varieties and more
than 1,760 species, were recently found in a virgin forest in a 29-
square-kilometer area in Luotian County.
</P>
<P>
Researchers have also discovered animals under state protection,
including rattlesnakes, leopards, parrots, owls and giant
salamanders.
</P>
<P>
Plants found include azaleas, ginkgoes, Chinese gooseberry and
haw.
</P>
<P>
The area is located on the highest peak of the mountain 1,404
meters above sea level.
</P>
<P>
Hubei Provincial Forestry Bureau and Central China Agriculture
University have designated the area as a botanical gene research
center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
