<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Regulate Parking Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- China's State Development
Planning Commission today announced the Measures on the Management
of Parking Rates for Motor Vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The measures, to be enforced from September 1 this year,
stipulate that the pricing policy on parking rate nationwide will
be decided by the central government while the actual rate will be
decided by local governments.
</P>
<P>
The rates at airports, railway stations, scenic spots and
residence area will be set by the government or in accordance with
government set prices. However, parking lots rates in shopping
malls, restaurants and office towers will be regulated by the
market.
</P>
<P>
The measures also stipulate that prices be written clearly for
all to see at parking lots, including rates for different type of
vehicles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
