<HEADLINE> China Opposes U.S. Allowing Chen Shui-bian to Make Stopover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has made
solemn representations to the United States for allowing Chen Shui-
bian of Taiwan to make a stopover in the U.S. on route to central
America in mid-August, expressing strong resentment and firm
opposition.
</P>
<P>
While commenting on the matter today, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao said that China has urged the U.S. to act as
it preaches, and honor the three Sino-U.S. joint communiques and
its relevant commitments, to avoid severely damaging bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan authorities often play tricks to conceal their real
motives in creating "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan". Zhu
said that the Chinese government has long opposed the U.S.
engaging in any official exchanges and contacts with Taiwan and
allowing Taiwan political figures to make a stopover in the U.S..
</P>
