<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Government Condemns Price-Fixing by TV Makers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has
overturned price-fixing launched by nine local color TV set
manufacturers, according to an official with the Ministry of
Information Industry.
</P>
<P>
At a recent discussion panel on regulating the color TV martet,
the nine pro-fixing companies agreed to stop interfering in price-
cuts by shops, the official said.
</P>
<P>
What these companies have done is against the Price Law and
must be halted immediately, the firms were told.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the discussion, the nine companies published a
joint declaration to support the government in controlling the
market.
</P>
<P>
On June 9, representatives from the nine manufacturers met to
discuss issues concerning the technical cooperation of color
television sets.
</P>
<P>
China, which turned out 44.86 million color TV sets last year,
is one of the largest home appliances producers in the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
