<DOCNO> XIE20000807.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CAS Concentrating Efforts on 746 Key Research Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS), the leading research institution in China, has been focusing
its resources on 746 key research programs in information, biology
and other high-tech areas over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
Shi Erwei, secretary-general of the CAS, said today the
programs were selected as the academy believes breakthroughs in
those programs will uplift its research capability in basic
sciences and facilitate economic and social development in China.
</P>
<P>
According to him, 654 of these programs are classified as
research in the new frontiers of science in an accordance with
global scientific and technological trends, 81 are selected with
an aim to make breakthrough; and the remaining 11 programs call
for joint efforts of several institutes and disciplines.
</P>
<P>
With a total cost of 820 million yuan (98 million U.S. dollars),
the programs involve research and development of biological chips,
micro communications satellites, nanometer materials, animal
cloning technology and environmental changes in western China, Shi
said.
</P>
<P>
The CAS also invested 810 million yuan (97 million U.S. dollars)
in building and upgrading research facilities such as the one for
controlled nuclear fusion. An additional 1.5 billion yuan (180.7
million U.S. dollars ) was used to improve working conditions and
to build housing projects for guest researchers in Beijing and
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
More than 6,000 elite scientists and researchers both at home
and abroad are involved in these programs, which are only part of
the CAS' knowledge innovation project, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
