<HEADLINE> Chinese Air Force Issues Code of Conduct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Air Force of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA) recently published a code of
conduct for its servicemen.
</P>
<P>
The code of conduct is called "Professional Ethics for Air
Force Servicemen and Professional Ethics for Major Troops."
</P>
<P>
Air Force personnel must be loyal to the Communist Party of
China, the country and the PLA, dedicated to the profession, look
after newly-recruited members and be respectful to their seniors,
according to it.
</P>
<P>
The newly-issued code of conduct is based on an experimental
code introduced in December 1998. 
