<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Says 160 Chechen Rebels Killed at Weekend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Russian military said Monday
that its artillery and air force killed about 160 rebels in the
republic of Chechnya during air strikes and shelling at the
weekend.
</P>
<P>
Powerful strikes were delivered against rebel groups in several
of the republic's districts, particularly north and northwest of
Gudermes, Nozhai-Yurt district and the Grozny district, the Itar-
Tass news agency quoted the office of the Russian presidential
aide on Chechnya, Sergei Yastrzhembsky, as saying on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The federal forces pounded rebel concentrations in the forests
near Chechnya's capital of Grozny, the second biggest city of
Gudermes, Nozhai-Yurt and Urus-Martan districts, killing more than
160 rebel fighters and mercenaries and wounding scores of others,
the Interfax news agency quoted the press center of the Russian
Combined Forces in the North Caucasus as saying.
</P>
<P>
The rebels' losses were especially severe in the forest north
of Gudermes, where Russian units found dozens of bodies of the
militants after federal artillery shelling and air raids,
according to the press center.
</P>
<P>
Russian air force killed over 40 rebels in Nozhai-Yurt, Urus-
Martan districts on Sunday. Su-25 attack planes flew four missions,
An-30 reconnaissance planes flew two, and Mi-8, Mi-24 and Mi-26
armed helicopters conducted 30 sorties over the districts,
destroying rebel targets, reconnoitering the areas, protecting
federal army convoys and transporting cargo.
</P>
<P>
The rebels, who had infiltrated neighboring Ingushetia and
fired at Russian helicopters several times Sunday, were killed in
a motor car while trying to escape. Under the rebels' fire, a
federal Mi-8 helicopter was forced to make an emergency landing
near a village in the Ingush republic's territory close to the
Chechen-Ingush border, with one of the 16 paratroopers on board
seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
On the whole, the rebels' threat to stage a large-scale
offensive on August 6, the so-called Ichkeria (rebels' Chechen
republic) Independence Day, did not materialize thanks to
preventive steps taken by the federal authorities, the press
center said.
</P>
<P>
There were no hit-and-run attacks or land mine explosions
reported in Grozny. Two militants were killed in the city Sunday
when they resisted federal troop's checking, Tass cited the press
center as saying, adding that eight members of Chechen warlord
Ruslan Gelayev's bandit group were captured and 12 people had been
detained in Achkhoi-Martan district on suspicion of involvement in
bandit formations.
</P>
<P>
"They said the federal forces have destroyed a large bandit
group numbering about 40 people not far from the administrative
border of Chechnya and Ingushetia," Yastrzhembsky's office said.
</P>
<P>
An influential Chechen rebel field commander, former chief of
the Ichkeria security service Ibragim Khultygov surrendered to
federal units, and well-known rebel field commander Wahhabbi
Musali Khaskhanov, an emir or "inspirer of a bandit group" was
also seized at the weekend, according to the office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
