<HEADLINE> Marine Tours to Viet Nam Via Beihai Popular </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIHAI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Marine tours to Viet Nam via
Beihai, a coastal city on Beibu Gulf in south China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, have become popular with Chinese,
especially those from Pearl River Delta in neighboring Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Huandao Shipping Company of Beihai, which
is authorized to operate the marine tours, said 13,000 Chinese
people took part in marine tours to Viet Nam in the first six
months of the year, 60 percent of whom were from Pearl River Delta.
The rest were from Chongqing, Chengdu, Beijing, Shanghai and Henan.
</P>
<P>
The company had to double its two return voyages to Viet Nam
every week as of July 13 to meet the growing demand. Tickets for
the tours during holidays are still hard to get and should be
booked two months in advance.
</P>
<P>
A corporate executive disclosed that they planned to purchase a
new and larger luxury passenger liner to replace the passenger
ship now in service. 
</P>
