Running on its fourth straight winning streak, the market was
of its largest rise since May 31, and was triggered to another
fresh high level within this year on buying spree. The recent
advance was met with little selling pressure as investors have not
been hesitant to commit, and at this rate, it is going to be easy
for the market to close on a very positive note.
</P>
<P>
A total of 54 issues advanced, with the remaining one unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Tire &AMP; Rubber, the bellwether of the market today, jumped 10.14
percent to 0.304 U.S. dollars, after the top tire maker in China
announced last Friday to sell its radial tire business to a 150
million U.S. dollars joint venture, in which France's Michelin &AMP;
Cie. SCA will hold a controlling 70 percent stake.
</P>
