<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market on Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- On Monday, the report on last
week's NAVs of new funds was released.
</P>
<P>
The composite indexes on the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock
markets increased 0.6 percent, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Among the 29 funds last week, 28 funds had their NAVs increased,
in particular, NAVs of 24 funds rose more than the composites
indexes on the two bourses. Fund Hanxing, Yuyang, Jinghong, and
Hansheng jumped three percent last week, much higher than the
composite indexes on the two stock markets.
</P>
<P>
Only Fund Jinding, which made its debut on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange last Friday, dropped in its NAV last week. Its NAV per
unit closed at 1.1735 yuan from the last Friday from the previous
1.1809 yuan.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, 22 discounted funds performed steadily on the China'
s securities investment fund market. Affected by rising NAVs, 21
funds rose moderately or kept unchanged. Only Fund Xinghe dropped,
down 0.01 yuan compared to the last close. The trading remained
calm and the turnover was contracted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
