<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Corsican Separatist Leader Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A former chief of Corsica's pro-
independence nationalist movement was shot dead Monday morning in
a bar on the island in the Mediterranean in a mafia-style
execution operation by five gunmen armed with automatic weapons,
said the gendarmerie.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Michel Rossi and his bodyguard, Jean-Claude Fratacci, were
gunned down in a bar in Upper-Corsica, when the gunmen arrived at
the bar on foot and spilled a wave of bullets on the facade and
terrace of the bar before entering the bar, where the two men were
sitting, said the gendarmerie quoting witnesses.
</P>
<P>
Rossi, 40, was a historic figure of the Corsican nationalist
movement and served as a leader of the National Liberation Front
of Corsica-Historical Trend until 1998.
</P>
<P>
French police are now unable to tell who could be responsible
for the assassination, but they said it is more probably a common
criminal case than one resulting from the political rivalry among
the Corsican nationalists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
