<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Edges South Korea 6-5 in World Junior Baseball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Canada's Brett Ralph had a two-run
triple in a 6-5 victory over South Korea in the world junior
baseball championships in Edmonton, Alberta on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The victory gave Canada a 2-1 record in the 12-team competition
and a share of the lead in the six-team Pool A with the United
States (2-0) and China (2-0). South Korea is 1-2, with South
Africa 0-2 and the Netherlands 0-3.
</P>
<P>
In Pool B, Australia leads with a 3-0 record, followed by
Mexico(2-1), Cuba (1-1), Chinese Taipei (1-1), Russia (1-2) and
Italy (0-3).
</P>
<P>
Australia ousted Cuba 5-4 in 10 innings, Chinese Taipei
defeated Italy 19-5 and Mexico eliminated Russia 13-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
