<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ICBC Sees Rise in Individual Consumption Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) said today that its individual consumption
loans have risen by a big margin in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that by the end of June, the bank's individual
housing loans increased 21.7 billion yuan (about 2.8 billion U.S.
dollars), or 13 billion yuan more than the same period last year,
while automobiles, durable goods wholesale consumption loans and
other kinds of individual consumption loans increased 5.1 billion
yuan, 4.4 billion yuan more than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ICBC that the bank's housing loans
maintained growth in the first half of the year. By the end of
June, the outstanding amount of individual housing loans reached
62.7 billion yuan, increasing 21.7 billion yuan from the beginning
of the year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, ICBC branches starting automobile consumption
loans expanded from 286 to 663, covering 35 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions across the country.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, the outstanding amount of automobile
consumption loans was 4.23 billion yuan. Durable goods wholesale
consumption loans reached 440 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC's individual consumption loans also include loans
pledged with petty deposits, comprehensive consumption loans,
tourism loans, petty short-term credit loans, state grant-in-aid
loans and loans to aid students studying overseas. By the end of
June, the ICBC had granted 10.87 billion yuan in such loans.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that in the second half of the year, the
ICBC will continue to promote consumption loans, with housing
loans being given top priority. The bank has decided to raise the
target for this year's individual housing loans from 36 billion
yuan to 55 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
