<HEADLINE> Shanghai A Shares End up Strongly on Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
closed at 2,039.42 points on Monday, up 13.06 points or 0.64
percent compared with the last close.
</P>
<P>
Total trading value was 12.88 billion yuan, 9.93 percent less
than last Friday's 14.3 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China'
s largest on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
After the Shanghai Composite Index consolidated between 2,017
points and 2,029 points Monday morning, it went up and reached the
highest level of 2,039.42 points at the day close.
</P>
<P>
As investors' sentiments were high, the market is likely to
continue to keep last week's new highs this week. Big player-held
shares and middle-priced shares became market leaders.
</P>
<P>
Three companies got to their up-limits, including Shanghai
Lingqiao Tap Water Co., Ltd. Harbin Churin Group Jointstock Co.,
Ltd. and Bohai Group Co., Ltd..
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Jinfeng Investment Co., Ltd. was the biggest loser
with its price down 5.85 percent to 24.96 yuan per share, hit by
profit taking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
