<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Up 2.54 Percent Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market index
gained 3 points, or 2.54 percent, to close at 121.39 Monday.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover was 140.59 million HK dollars, which was about
21.15 million HK dollars or 17.71 percent more than the total of
last Friday, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities information provider.
</P>
<P>
The market managed to get rid of rang-bound trading and posted
its strongest rise since June 21. It is also the first time since
June 7 for the market to breach the important 120-point level.
Recent attempt at all-around rally seems to have set in motion for
now.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outpaced declining shares by 48 to 5, with 3
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
North Jianshe climbed 7.79 percent to 1.66 HK dollars, while
Hefei Meiling rose 6.28 percent to 2.20 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sez Real Estate fell 1.57 percent to 2.50 HK dollars, while
Health Mineral shed 0.49 percent to 4.05 HK dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
