<HEADLINE> Appointment of Thai Senate President and Vice Presidents Officially Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 7 (Xinhua) -- His Majesty King Bhumibol
Adulyadej has approved the appointment of President and Vice
Presidents of Thailand's first elected Senate, the Thai News
Agency (TNA) reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
His Majesty the King endorsed on August 4 the appointment of
Sanit Vorapanya, a senator from Lopburi province, as President of
Thailand's first-ever elected Senate, and Chalerm Promlert and
Buntan Dokthaisong as the Senate's First and Second Vice
Presidents respectively, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The royal approval followed secret votes by all 200 elected
senators at their first meeting here on August 1 to select the
Senate's Speaker and Vice Speakers.
</P>
<P>
The country organized its first senatorial election on March 4,
which was part of a political reform, aimed to eliminate vote
buying and other irregular practices, and create free and fair
elections eventually.
</P>
<P>
The March 4 poll was, however, followed by four senatorial by-
elections in some provinces due to suspension of elected
candidates for found evidences of frauds and forms of vote buying.
</P>
<P>
The 200-seat Senate was completed in late July, after the last
elected candidate in the northeastern province of Ubon Rachathani
was unanimously endorsed by the Election Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
