<DOCNO> XIE20000807.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Exports to United States Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has made progress in
boosting exports to the United States although the country has not
yet been given normal trade relation status by the United States.
</P>
<P>
According to Vietnam News Agency, Vietnam's exports to the
United States have been increasing in recent years. Vietnam's
export earnings rose to 504 million U.S. dollars last year from 50.
4 million U.S. dollars in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The volume of goods worth 305 million U.S. dollars was exported
to the United States in the first six months of this year. The
United States is currently ranked Vietnam's seventh biggest trade
partner.
</P>
<P>
Seafood took the lead among the country's exports to the United
States, with total export value registered at 125.5 million U.S.
dollars in 1999 (equal to 25 per cent of the country's export
value to the United States).
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese seafood export to U.S. market valued at 118 million
U.S dollars in the first half of this year, increasing over 60
times in the 1994-1999 period.
</P>
<P>
Footwear was ranked second among Vietnamese exports to the U.S.
market with an export value of 102.6 million U.S. dollars last
year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese crude oil exporters registered an export value of 38.
4 million U.S. dollars from selling 194,163 tonnes of crude to the
United States in the first half of this year. As a result, the
United States becomes Vietnam's third biggest oil importer.
</P>
<P>
Ranking fourth among the country's exports to the U.S. market
was coffee. Vietnam attained a coffee export value of 59.2 million
U.S. dollars and over 26.2 million U.S. dollars last year and in
the first half of the year 2000 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Garments and Textile products have been Vietnam's major export
items in recent years, but local exporters earned only 34.7
million U.S. dollars and 25.4 million U.S. dollars from exporting
garments and textile products to the United States last year and
in the first half of this year respectively.
</P>
<P>
Other products such as cashew nut, pepper, rice, handicrafts,
fresh and dried fruits from Vietnam have made their debut in the U.
S. market. However, their export volume and value remained low.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
