<HEADLINE> Manila Stocks Fall Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in the Philippine
Stock Exchange fell Monday on lack of fresh news to spur market
activity.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, dropped 1.08
points to close at 1,450.10. However, the broader all-shares index
rose 3.24 points to 628.97.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 457 million shares worth some 7.65 million U.
S. dollars on Monday against last Friday's 594 million shares
worth some 13 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said investors are still waiting for strong economic
fundamentals to turn them in the buying mood.
</P>
<P>
They added that provisions in the new Securities Law
prohibiting brokerage houses to trade their holdings also
contributed to weak market activity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
