<HEADLINE> Chinese DVD Player Producer Gets Credit Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Jiangsu Hongtu High Technology
Company Limited, a major Chinese digital video disc (DVD) player
manufacturer, has been given credit support from a bank for its
complete machines exports.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed here recently, Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) Shanghai Branch will provide an
additional credit line of 63.42 million U.S. dollars to Hongtu.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bank will provide the company, which is based in
east China's Jiangsu Province, a credit line worth 50 million U.S.
dollars for the establishment of a letter of credit.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai World Trade Development Co. Ltd. and APEX Digital Inc.
of the United States will be responsible for the sales of DVD
players produced by Hongtu.
</P>
<P>
A well-known company listed in a Chinese bourse, Hongtu's sales
volume exceeded 760 million yuan last year, jumping 90 percent
over the previous year, said Liu Xiaofeng, chairman of Hongtu.
</P>
<P>
Liu predicted that the demand for DVD players may stand at
around 10 million sets this year, 60 percent of which comes from
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The exports of DVD players have become a driving force behind
the growth of China's exports, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
