<HEADLINE> Sino-U.S. Postgraduate Program Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Donghua University of China and
Boston University of the United States today signed an agreement
to launch a joint postgraduate program in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Boston University has signed such an
agreement with a Chinese university. It is designed to train both
Masters of Business Administration (MBA) and Executive Masters Of
Business Administration (EMBA).
</P>
<P>
It is aimed at meeting a worldwide increasing demand for high-
ranking managerial personnel.
</P>
<P>
Donghua sources said the program will adopt the core curriculum
from Boston University and hire professors from the United States.
</P>
<P>
Students will mainly be selected from among multinational
executives, managers of large Chinese enterprises, and government
officials. 
