<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Street Relic of Tang Dynasty Discovered in Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAODING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A portion of an ancient street,
believed to have been built in the Tang Dynasty (618-907) was
discovered in Baoding in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Lying 5.25 meters underground, the street runs in an east-west
direction. It is 20 centimeters thick, and still has its distinct
marks from wheels that had traveled upon it, according to a local
cultural relic department.
</P>
<P>
Some remnants of china, made during the Tang Dynasty, were also
found in the soil and experts inferred that the street is from the
Tang Dynasty as well.
</P>
<P>
The street has not been completely unearthed, but experts say
it is five meters wide, but its length has yet to be determined.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000807.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Social Security Fund to Boost China's Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- China's bullish stock market may
get a further lift in the near future since the government is
already studying the possibility of investing social security
funds into the securities market.
</P>
<P>
According to today's China Securities, the Ministry of Labor
and Social Security has started a program to research the income
and expenditure of social security funds over the next three to
five years, as well as investment and risk control in social
security fund management.
</P>
<P>
The program will be done in co-operation with the Beijing-based
Boshi Fund Management Co., which now manages five closed-end funds
with total net assets worth 10 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted experts as saying that social security fund
has the potential of becoming a major source of capital for China'
s stock market.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jianlun, vice-minister of Labor and Social Security said
the design of China's social security system will be completed
within the year and put into test operation in 2001. 
</P>
