<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Highlights of Major Trade-related News (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The U.S. fast food giant Kentucky Fried Chicken (KFC) has
increased its outlets in China to 370 since its first restaurant
opened in Beijing in 1987. At present, the Chinese capital city
alone has had 45 KFC restaurants, employing 25,000 people. The
remaining outlets scatter in 90 other cities across China.
</P>
<P>
-- China and Uzbekistan established their first joint venture,
the Uzbek Market Co., Ltd., recently in an effort to strengthen
the two countries' economic links. The Shanghai-based new joint
venture is a result of joint efforts from six Uzbek companies and
Chinese companies including Shenli Group based in central China's
Henan Province and the Chinatex Non-Cotton Yarns and Fabrics
Import and Export Corporation.
</P>
<P>
-- Three major local automotive manufacturers set up a joint
venture sales company last Tuesday. The Shanghai Volkswagen Sales
Co. Ltd. was jointly set up by Shanghai Automotive Industry (Group)
Co., Shanghai Volkswagen Investment Co. Ltd. and Shanghai
Volkswagen Co. Ltd. With a total investment of 29.98 million U.S.
dollars, the sales company will use the global sales network of
Volkswagen to sell Passat cars manufactured in Shanghai.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
