<HEADLINE> Indonesia Determined to Carry Out Reforms: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Abdurrahman
Wahid Monday stressed that the government is determined to carry
out the reforms.
</P>
<P>
"The government's resolve and determination to continue
overcoming the crisis, safeguarding the national integrity and
carrying out the reforms will ever be incessant, no matter how
dreadful the problems and challenges are which we are confronting,
" the president said in his working report to the annual general
session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR).
</P>
<P>
The president also said the government will endure its deep
commitment to keep on developing democratic life, human rights,
justice, supremacy of law, social welfare, regional autonomy,
stability and social order.
</P>
<P>
"Actually, these major tasks should be carried out by the
entire people of Indonesia. Of course the government plays a key
role in encouraging the components of the society in a bid to take
an active part and give their contribution (to overcoming the
crisis)," Wahid said.
</P>
<P>
The president's report was read out by Cabinet Secretary
Marsilam Simanjuntak before the members of MPR following the
opening ceremony of the first ever MPR annual general session
which will last until August 18.
</P>
<P>
The president said the government remains unbending to carry
through its resolve to take any appropriate chances to bring the
country and the nation out of the lingering multidimensional
crisis. The government's policies and measures to consistently
bring into existence a clean and good governance will continue to
progress.
</P>
<P>
"This will be carried out mainly through the performing of
steady and justifiable measures to put an end to the KKN (
corruption, collusion and nepotism) practices in the government's
institutions, to improve the judiciary institutions' independence
followed by the refined professionalism and moral integrity, and
to improve transparency in information and policy making," he said.
</P>
<P>
To resolve the problems, the president asked the Indonesian
people to give full support to the government.
</P>
<P>
The president assured that the government would work even
harder and proceed to strive for more accomplishment.
</P>
<P>
"More than 200 million Indonesian people will be very thankful
and glad should, through wisdom, intelligence and compassion, we
be able to produce a genuine national solution in an orderly,
democratic as well as decent and ethical manner, for otherwise, we
would fail to build consensus and find an accurate solution," he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
