<HEADLINE> Capello Wins Mosport Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Rinaldo Capello of Italy beat
Jorg Muller's BMW to win the Grand Prix at Mosport sports car race
at Mosport International Raceway in Bowmanville, Ontario on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian nursed his Audi R8 prototype around the course on
rain tires because the track was initially wet, but still won.
</P>
<P>
Capello, who teamed with Allan McNish for the Audi triumph,
posted the closest finish in American Le Mans Series history,
beating Muller to the line by just .148 of a second.
</P>
<P>
The McNish-Capello machine led the last 35 laps, but the last
one offered the breathtaking finish.
</P>
<P>
Muller was on dry tires and was reeling in Capello at the rate
of four to seven seconds a lap. He caught Capello at Turn 3, then
waited until the final corner to make a move, diving under Capello
and just missing victory at the line.
</P>
<P>
McNish set the fastest lap in Mosport history in race
competition with a speed of 123.942 mph (199 kph) on the sixth lap
of the race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
