<HEADLINE> E-Gateway for Equity Market Developed in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's national news
agency Bernama, a major news and financial information services
provider, announced Monday that it has introduced Dragonshare.com,
an e-gateway to Malaysia's equity market.
</P>
<P>
Investors who register with Dragonshare have free access to
real-time quotes from stock exchanges in Malaysia and Singapore,
charts market commentaries and financial news from its wire
services, Bernama said in a statement here.
</P>
<P>
Among the services offered on the portal are a suite of
information modules, analytics, an online trading application and
a direct connection with a broker and an order routing module
allows investors and brokers to transact the buying and selling of
shares, update cash accounts and portfolios and confirm and cancel
orders entirely online and in real-time.
</P>
<P>
Customers in different time zones can key in orders overnight
for processing the next morning and at a low cost since it is done
through low international Internet charges.
</P>
<P>
Security is tight on Dragonshare which is backed by the Secure
Socket Layer (SSL) protocol for transmitting private documents and
U.S. government-approved encryption techniques for verifying and
authenticating identities, it said.
</P>
<P>
Brokers and remisiers are encouraged to register now to take
advantage of the site's 'Dragon Year' promotion during which they
get a free service for three months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
