<HEADLINE> Thailand Joins Hands With Neighbors in Developing Regional Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will help four
neighboring countries in Southeast Asia in developing their trade
and investment in the manufacturing sector, which will lead to
more developed and liberalized trade and investment in the region
in the future, the Thai News Agency (TNA) reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Director-General of the Department of Business Economics Karun
Kittisataporn was quoted as saying that the move is part of an
economic cooperation framework between Thailand and the four
neighboring countries, that is, Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar and
Vietnam, aimed to help the four new members of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) to develop their trade and
investment in their manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation would eventually lead to the four countries'
more active roles in promoting and strengthening trade and
investment, particularly in the manufacturing sector, for the
whole region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's cooperation would cover organizing workshops and
training programs for personnel of the four countries, and
exchanging information and ideas that would be useful for the
development of regional trade and investment, he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Issues of business registrations, privatization of state
enterprises, and measures to develop human resources, as well as
trade and investment system would be included in the workshops and
training programs, said Karun.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation will not only help strengthen ties between Thai
officials and personnel and their counterparts in the four
countries, but also enhance their work efficiency and encourage
exchanges of information on measures and policies concerning trade
and investment, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Karun pointed out that the cooperation is believed to
eventually lead to more developed and liberalized trade and
investment in the ASEAN. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
