<HEADLINE> Germany Sees More Neo-Nazi Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The neo-Nazi and far-right
violence erupted sporadically over the weekend in Germany, media
reports said.
</P>
<P>
In the eastern town of Gera, five neo-Nazis beat up two
Pakistanis at a restaurant. All five suspects were arrested. Three
of them are to appear before a court.
</P>
<P>
In the western city of Bochum, 16 young people, aged 13 to 23,
attacked an African after a church was dedicated.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in the northeastern city of Rostock, 36 youths have
been remanded in custody in connection with the attack against an
anti-fascist exhibition.
</P>
<P>
In the northern town of Tostedt, some 250 right-wingers clashed
with 100 left-wingers on the streets. About 300 of them were
arrested.
</P>
<P>
Neo-Nazi attacks have increased in Germany over recent months.
</P>
<P>
On July 27, 10 Jewish immigrants were injured when a bomb
exploded in Dusseldorf, western Germany.
</P>
<P>
Alarmed at the upsurge of extreme right-wing violence, German
political leaders and personalities are calling for decisive
action against the terror tactics of neo-Nazi and skinheads
against foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Some even urged to mobilize federal frontier troops to quench
the violence. 
</P>
