close the gap with Bush in the next two weeks as he chooses a
running mate and then heads to Los Angeles for the Democratic
National Convention.
</P>
<P>
Gore planned to announce his running mate Tuesday in his home
state of Tennessee, a week before the Democratic National
Convention opens in Los Angeles to nominate him and his running
mate for 2000 presidential election.
</P>
<P>
Gore met Sunday with the head of his vice presidential search
effort as attention focused on four Democratic senators, Evan Bayh
of Indiana, John Edwards of North Carolina, John Kerry of
Massachusetts and Joseph Lieberman of Connecticut.
</P>
