<HEADLINE> Williams Beats Seles in Carlsbad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
WASHINGTON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Venus Williams defeated
Monica Seles 6-0, 6-7 (3-7), 6-3 on Sunday to capture the 535,000
U.S. dollar tournament in Carlsbad for her third consecutive
singles title.
</P>
<P>
Williams, beaten by world number one Martina Hingis in last
year's final, earned 87,000 U.S.dollars, following titles at
Wimbledon and the Bank of the West Classic -- both over second-
ranked Linsay Davenport, reports said.
</P>
<P>
On her way to the final, Williams, ranked third and seeded the
same, brushed aside Amanda Coetzer of South Africa, fifth seed
Spaniard Conchita Martinez and giant-killer Amy Frazier, who
stunned Hingis in a quarter-final match.
</P>
<P>
Seles, ranked sixth and seeded fourth, was vying for her
fourth title of the year. But the nine-time Grand Slam winner
dropped to 0-3 lifetime against her Sydney Olympic teammate.
</P>
</TEXT>
