<HEADLINE> Arafat Arrives in Qatar to Rally Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
arrived in Qatar Monday to continue his support-rallying campaign
after the failure of the Camp David talks with Israel in the U.S..
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived here Monday night from the United Arab Emirates
for a two-day visit and he will hold talks with Qatari Crown Prince
Sheikh Jassem bin Hamad al-Thani first due to the absence of Emir
Sheikh Hamad bin Khalifa al-Thani, the official Qatari news agency
QNA said.
</P>
<P>
Hamad, who is in Sudan on a mediation mission between Sudan and
Eritrea, may return Tuesday to meet Arafat, diplomats in Doha said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat began a tour to Arab and Islamic countries to rally
support after the talks with Israel in Camp David near Washington
fell apart last week. The talks had been designed to come up with
consensus between Israel and the Palestinians over final status
issues to lay ground for a permanent peace deal by September.
</P>
<P>
But the two sides failed to solve their difference over the core
issues, especially the fate of Jerusalem. Israel proposed a shared
sovereignty over Arab East Jerusalem, which was rejected by the
Palestinians who want the whole east part under their total
sovereignty.  
</P>
</TEXT>
