<HEADLINE> Venezuelan President to Defend Oil Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Strengthening the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) and supporting the oil price
defense system are the two issues to be examined by Venezuelan
President Hugo Chavez during his trip to the Middle East, Africa
and Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
Chavez, who departed last Sunday, will meet with the heads of
state of OPEC member countries: Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, Qatar,
United Arab Emirates, Iran, Iraq, Indonesia, Nigeria and Algeria.
</P>
<P>
His trip is designed to strengthen the consensus-building
mechanism relating to production quotas so as to strike a balance
in the oil market and defend the appropriate oil prices, explained
President Chavez.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela's Energy and Mining Minister and current OPEC
president Ali Rodriguez said oil prices will continue to range
between 22 and 28 dollars per barrel. 
