<HEADLINE> Fire-Fighting Plane Crash Kills Pilot in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The pilot of a Greek fire-
fighting plane was killed Monday night when his plane crashed in
the country's northwestern island of Corfu during an operation to
combat a forest fire.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old pilot was taking part with two helicopters in
extinguishing the fire in the area of Paleokastritsa, the semi-
official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
It is the second such incident in Greece within one month. On
July 8, two Greek pilots died when their "Canadair" fire-fighting
plane crashed during an operation to put out a forest fire in
central Greece. 
</P>
