<HEADLINE> European Major Stock Markets End Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 7 (Xinhua) - Europe's major stock markets closed
higher Monday buoyed by banks, drugs and oil stocks and growing
hopes that the worst was over for U.S. interest rates.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index ended up 24.3 points or 0.4 percent at
6387.8, after trading inside a narrow 45-point band throughout the
session near the middle of its 6200-6600 range.
</P>
<P>
