percent, to end at 7113.22, led by banking stocks such as Dresdner
Bank and Hypovereinsbank.
</P>
<P>
The Paris CAC-40 added 0.9 percent up to 6519.04, with the
Dutch data network operator Equant gaining 5.3 percent to lead the
gainers.  
