<HEADLINE> Uganda Earns 13 Million U.S. Dollars From Coffee Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Uganda earned 13.45 million U.S.
dollars from exports of 291,029 bags of coffee in July this year,
according to a monthly report available on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The monthly report released by Uganda Coffee Development
Authority (UCDA) for July says that this earning represents an
increase of 9 percent from the 12.35 million dollars in June.
</P>
<P>
The report says, however, the volume and value fell by 14.9
percent and 38.1 percent respectively, compared with exports in
July of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Cumulatively, the total export since last October amounted to 2,
465,396 bags valued at 146.1 million dollars as compared with 3,
125,326 bags worth 250.5 million dollars in the previous
corresponding period.
</P>
<P>
The reduction in volume is attributed to the prolonged dry
weather in the central and eastern regions of Uganda, and the
value decline was due to the falling coffee price on the world
market.
</P>
<P>
Coffee export is a major foreign exchange earner of the east
Africa country, accounting for 60 percent of the country's total
foreign exchange earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
