<HEADLINE> Uruguay's Wool Exports Up Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay's wool exports in the
1999-2000 wool-making season rose 20 percent over the last season,
the Uruguayan Wool Department said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Dirty wool exports reached 5.8 million kilograms, a 22.9
increase over last season's level. Washed wool exports increased
23.8 percent to 4.02 million kilograms, and industrialized wool
went up by 21.8 percent to 44.7 million kilograms.
</P>
<P>
China was the largest dirty wool importer: 45.85 percent of its
import being dirty wool or 90.4 percent over last season's level.
It was followed by Italy, Germany, Iran and Great Britain.
</P>
<P>
Of the total dirty wool export, 85.9 percent went to China, 6.4
percent to Colombia and 3 percent to Belgium.
</P>
<P>
As for washed wool exports, Germany received 45.4 percent,
Italy 29.9 percent and Spain 8.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
