<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Inter-State Road Transit Scheme Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The inter-state road transit scheme
was put into operation here on Monday to facilitate the free
movement of goods and personnel within the 16-member Economic
Community of the West African States (ECOWAS).
</P>
<P>
Nigerian Minister of Transport Chief Ojo Maduekwe said on
behalf of President Olusegun Obasanjo at the launching ceremony at
Seme Border Town outside Lagos that the scheme is aimed at pushing
forward the integration process of the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
The inter-state road transit scheme is a major program of the "
Nigeria-Ghana Fast Track Approach" toward the realization of
integration objectives in the sub-region, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria is the first country in the ECOWAS to remove all
checkpoints along its highways, except at the border posts, to
facilitate the free movement of inter-state goods. 
</P>
